Going to get my baby back home

The original Leiber/Stroller composition as performed by the likes of Fats Domino and Wilfred Harrison includes lyrics like “They got some crazy little women there/And I’m gonna get me one” and “If I stay with that woman, I know I’m going to die”. This Beatles re-write however changes that completely: it is not about getting a new partner from Kansas City, but regaining an old love (early renditions talk negatively about the ex, rather than try to get her love.
